Frontend Dockerfile:
- Node build stage
- NGINX serve stage
- static build
- healthcheck

NGINX:
- reverse proxy /api/* to backend:8005
- serve frontend
- security headers
- request size limits
- optional gzip
- WebSocket-ready proxy config
- no secrets embedded

Backup:
infra/scripts/backup-postgres.sh
- uses pg_dump
- outputs timestamped .sql.gz
- keeps backups under ./backups
- supports retention days
- no hardcoded passwords
- reads env vars

Restore:
infra/scripts/restore-postgres.sh
- restores from backup file
- requires RESTORE_CONFIRM=yes
- fails safely if file missing
- no hardcoded passwords

CI:
- backend-tests
- frontend-tests
- docker-build
- no real external APIs required

